# HQ - Harness Orchestrator & Dashboard

## Vision

**HQ** (Headquarters) is a native desktop application that provides a visual dashboard for managing AI agent development sessions. It enables developers to orchestrate, monitor, and control multiple Claude Code sessions across different projects without using a terminal.

## Important Distinction: Three Separate Concepts

Understanding HQ requires separating three distinct concepts:

| Concept | What It Is | Example |
|---------|------------|---------|
| **Harness (method)** | A pattern for AI agents to work on long tasks across sessions via state files | `.harness/progress.txt` + `features.json` |
| **HQ in development** | This project is being BUILT using the Harness method | The `.harness/` folder in THIS repo |
| **HQ as product** | Once built, HQ will MANAGE other projects that use Harness | Visual dashboard for external projects |

**Key insight:** The `.harness/` folder here is for building HQ itself. When HQ is complete, it will open and visualize `.harness/` folders from OTHER projects.

---

## Core Philosophy

> "A Single Pane of Glass for AI-Assisted Development"

HQ transforms the way developers interact with long-running AI agents by providing:
- **Visual Kanban boards** for feature tracking
- **Real-time logs** from all running processes
- **PTY-based process control** with full interactivity
- **Multi-project management** via tabs
- **Harness state visualization**

---

## Architecture Overview

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                         HQ Desktop App                               │
│                    (Tauri + React 19 + PatternFly 6)                 │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                      │
│  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │
│  │   Tab Bar      │  │   Kanban View   │  │   Logs Panel           │ │
│  │   (Projects)   │  │   (Features)    │  │   (Real-time PTY)      │ │
│  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘  └────────────────────────┘ │
│                                                                      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                       State Management Layer                         │
│                  (@zazcart/tools state-machine)                    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                       Rust Backend (Tauri)                           │
│                                                                      │
│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐  │
│  │ PTY Controller  │  │ File Watcher    │  │ IPC Commands        │  │
│  │ (portable-pty)  │  │ (notify crate)  │  │ (Tauri invoke)      │  │
│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘  │
│                                                                      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                     External Processes                               │
│                                                                      │
│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐  │
│  │ Claude Code #1  │  │ Claude Code #2  │  │ Other Processes     │  │
│  │ (Project A)     │  │ (Project B)     │  │ (servers, tests)    │  │
│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘  │
│                                                                      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Technology Stack

| Layer                | Technology          | Version | Purpose                              |
|----------------------|---------------------|---------|--------------------------------------|
| **Desktop Runtime**  | Tauri               | 2.x     | Native app shell, Rust backend       |
| **Frontend**         | React               | 19.x    | UI framework                         |
| **UI Components**    | PatternFly          | 6.x     | Enterprise UI (chat, terminal, logs) |
| **State Management** | @zazcart/tools      | 0.1.0   | State machine + schema validation    |
| **PTY Emulation**    | portable-pty (Rust) | latest  | Process spawning and control         |
| **File Watching**    | notify (Rust)       | latest  | Real-time harness file changes       |
| **IPC**              | Tauri Commands      | -       | Frontend ↔ Backend communication     |

### Why PatternFly 6?

PatternFly provides ready-made components for our use cases:
- **Chat/AI components** - For agent communication UI
- **Log viewer** - Real-time log display with ANSI support
- **Terminal** - Embedded terminal views
- **Tabs** - Multi-project navigation
- **Cards/Panels** - Kanban board layout
- **Dark theme** - Built-in dark mode support

---

## Feature Specifications

### F001: Multi-Project Tab Management

**Description:** Open and manage multiple projects simultaneously via tabs.

**UI Elements:**
- Tab bar at top (PatternFly Tabs)
- New tab button (+)
- Close tab button (X)
- Tab context menu (rename, close others, close all)

**Behavior:**
- Each tab represents a project directory
- Tab title shows project name (from package.json or folder name)
- Active tab is highlighted
- Tabs are reorderable via drag-and-drop

### F002: Kanban Board View

**Description:** Visual kanban board for feature tracking within a project.

**Columns:**
```
BACKLOG → TODO → DOING → REVIEW → QA → DONE
```

**Card Structure:**
- Feature ID (e.g., F001)
- Title
- Description (truncated)
- Status badge
- Priority indicator
- Click to expand details

**Data Source:**
- Reads from `.harness/features.json`
- Auto-updates when file changes (via file watcher)
- Status mapped to columns:
  - `passes: false` + not started → BACKLOG
  - `passes: false` + priority → TODO
  - `passes: false` + in_progress → DOING
  - `passes: false` + needs_review → REVIEW
  - `passes: false` + testing → QA
  - `passes: true` → DONE

### F003: Real-Time Log Panel

**Description:** Live output from running processes (Claude Code, servers, etc.)

**Features:**
- PatternFly LogViewer component
- ANSI color support
- Timestamp prefix
- Process filter
- Search within logs
- Clear button
- Auto-scroll toggle

**Technical:**
- PTY streams → Tauri events → React state
- Max 10,000 lines per process (ring buffer)

### F004: PTY Process Controller

**Description:** Spawn, control, and interact with shell processes.

**Capabilities:**
- Start new process (e.g., `claude` command)
- Send keystrokes (including Ctrl+C, Ctrl+D)
- Resize PTY on window resize
- Kill process
- Restart process

**Rust Implementation:**
```rust
use portable_pty::{CommandBuilder, PtySize, native_pty_system};

fn spawn_process(cmd: &str, cols: u16, rows: u16) -> Result<PtyPair> {
    let pty_system = native_pty_system();
    let pair = pty_system.openpty(PtySize { rows, cols, .. })?;
    let cmd = CommandBuilder::new(cmd);
    pair.slave.spawn_command(cmd)?;
    Ok(pair)
}
```

### F005: Harness State Visualization

**Description:** Display current harness state visually.

**Components:**
- Progress summary card
  - Features completed / total
  - Current session info
  - Last commit
- Active feature highlight
- Session timeline (from progress.txt)

### F006: Project Selector Dialog

**Description:** Open new project from file system.

**UI:**
- PatternFly Modal
- Recent projects list
- Browse button (native file picker via Tauri)
- Validate project (check for .harness folder)

### F007: Settings Panel

**Description:** Configure HQ preferences.

**Settings:**
- Theme (light/dark/system)
- Log buffer size
- Auto-start Claude Code
- Default shell
- Font size

---

## State Management (using @zazcart/tools)

### Schema Validation

```typescript
import { createModel, InferType } from '@zazcart/tools';

// Project Schema - using string-based type definitions
const ProjectSchema = createModel({
  id: 'string',
  path: 'string',
  name: 'string',
  harness: {
    properties: {
      progressFile: 'string',
      featuresFile: 'string',
    },
  },
});

type Project = InferType<typeof ProjectSchema>;

// Feature Schema (from harness)
const FeatureSchema = createModel({
  id: 'string',
  description: 'string',
  category: 'string',
  passes: 'boolean',
  steps: 'string[]',
});

type Feature = InferType<typeof FeatureSchema>;

// Process Schema
const ProcessSchema = createModel({
  id: 'string',
  projectId: 'string',
  command: 'string',
  status: { enum: ['running', 'stopped', 'error'] },
  pid: 'number?', // optional
});

type Process = InferType<typeof ProcessSchema>;

// Validation usage
const project = ProjectSchema.parse(rawData);     // throws on invalid
const isValid = ProjectSchema.isValid(rawData);   // returns boolean
```

### State Machine

```typescript
import { createMachine, createSlice, createAsyncSlice } from '@zazcart/tools';
import { invoke } from '@tauri-apps/api/core';

// UI Slice - synchronous state with reducers
const uiSlice = createSlice({
  id: 'ui',
  cache: { policy: 'session' },
  initial: {
    activeTab: '',
    theme: 'system' as 'light' | 'dark' | 'system',
    projectOrder: [] as string[],
  },
  reducers: {
    setActiveTab: (state, tabId: string) => {
      state.activeTab = tabId;
    },
    setTheme: (state, theme: 'light' | 'dark' | 'system') => {
      state.theme = theme;
    },
    addProject: (state, projectId: string) => {
      state.projectOrder.push(projectId);
    },
    removeProject: (state, projectId: string) => {
      state.projectOrder = state.projectOrder.filter((id) => id !== projectId);
    },
    reorderProjects: (state, order: string[]) => {
      state.projectOrder = order;
    },
  },
});

// Projects Slice - synchronous state for project data
const projectsSlice = createSlice({
  id: 'projects',
  cache: { policy: 'private' },
  initial: {} as Record<string, Project>,
  reducers: {
    set: (state, project: Project) => {
      state[project.id] = project;
    },
    remove: (state, projectId: string) => {
      delete state[projectId];
    },
  },
});

// Processes Slice - for PTY process tracking
const processesSlice = createSlice({
  id: 'processes',
  cache: { policy: 'session' },
  initial: {} as Record<string, Process>,
  reducers: {
    spawn: (state, process: Process) => {
      state[process.id] = process;
    },
    updateStatus: (state, payload: { id: string; status: Process['status'] }) => {
      if (state[payload.id]) {
        state[payload.id].status = payload.status;
      }
    },
    kill: (state, processId: string) => {
      delete state[processId];
    },
  },
});

// Features Slice - async slice for fetching harness features
const featuresSlice = createAsyncSlice({
  id: 'features',
  cache: { policy: 'private' },
  context: {},
  // The load function fetches data - called when actions.load() is dispatched
  async load(projectPath: string) {
    const response = await invoke('harness:read_features', { path: projectPath });
    return response as Feature[];
  },
});

// Async slice state shape:
// {
//   loading: boolean,   // true while load() is running
//   loaded: boolean,    // true after successful load
//   failed: boolean,    // true if load() threw
//   error: string|null, // error message if failed
//   value: T|null,      // the loaded data
//   changes: number,    // increment counter
// }

// Async slice auto-generated actions:
// - actions.load(payload)  → triggers load function, sets loading=true
// - actions.success(data)  → sets value, loaded=true
// - actions.fail({ error }) → sets error, failed=true
// - actions.clear()        → resets to initial state

// Create the app machine
const appMachine = createMachine({
  id: 'app',
  slices: {
    ui: uiSlice,
    projects: projectsSlice,
    processes: processesSlice,
    features: featuresSlice,
  },
  context: {
    userID: null,
  },
});

export { appMachine };
```

### React Integration

```typescript
// Using useMachine hook - returns { state, actions }
function TabBar() {
  const { state, actions } = appMachine.useMachine('ui');

  return (
    <div>
      {state.projectOrder.map((id) => (
        <Tab
          key={id}
          active={id === state.activeTab}
          onClick={() => actions.setActiveTab(id)}
          onClose={() => actions.removeProject(id)}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

// Using useSelector for derived state
function ProjectCount() {
  const count = appMachine.useSelector((state) => state.ui.projectOrder.length);
  return <span>{count} projects</span>;
}

// Accessing multiple slices
function ProcessPanel() {
  const { state: processes, actions } = appMachine.useMachine('processes');
  const { state: ui } = appMachine.useMachine('ui');

  const activeProcesses = Object.values(processes).filter(
    (p) => p.projectId === ui.activeTab
  );

  return (
    <div>
      {activeProcesses.map((process) => (
        <ProcessCard
          key={process.id}
          process={process}
          onKill={() => actions.kill(process.id)}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

// Using async slice - handles loading/error states
function FeatureBoard({ projectPath }: { projectPath: string }) {
  const { state, actions } = appMachine.useMachine('features');

  // Trigger load on mount or path change
  React.useEffect(() => {
    actions.load(projectPath);
  }, [projectPath]);

  if (state.loading) {
    return <Spinner />;
  }

  if (state.failed) {
    return (
      <Alert variant="danger">
        {state.error}
        <Button onClick={() => actions.load(projectPath)}>Retry</Button>
      </Alert>
    );
  }

  if (!state.loaded || !state.value) {
    return <EmptyState>No features loaded</EmptyState>;
  }

  return (
    <KanbanBoard>
      {state.value.map((feature) => (
        <FeatureCard key={feature.id} feature={feature} />
      ))}
    </KanbanBoard>
  );
}
```

### Cache Policies

| Policy    | Behavior                                      |
|-----------|-----------------------------------------------|
| `public`  | Shared across all users, persisted            |
| `private` | Per-user, persisted (invalidates on userID change) |
| `session` | Per-session, cleared on app restart           |

---

## Tauri Commands (IPC)

```typescript
// Frontend → Backend commands
interface TauriCommands {
  'project:open': (path: string) => Promise<Project>;
  'project:close': (id: string) => Promise<void>;
  'pty:spawn': (projectId: string, cmd: string) => Promise<string>;
  'pty:write': (processId: string, data: string) => Promise<void>;
  'pty:resize': (processId: string, cols: number, rows: number) => Promise<void>;
  'pty:kill': (processId: string) => Promise<void>;
  'harness:read_features': (path: string) => Promise<Feature[]>;
  'harness:watch': (projectPath: string) => Promise<void>;
  'fs:select_directory': () => Promise<string | null>;
}

// Backend → Frontend events
interface TauriEvents {
  'pty:output': { processId: string; data: string };
  'pty:exit': { processId: string; code: number };
  'harness:changed': { projectPath: string; file: string };
}
```

---

